      "eligibilityCriteria": {
        "eligibilityDescription_md": "\n   1. The applicant should be a permanent resident of Meghalaya.\n   1. The applicant who wants to become a teacher may apply for the scheme.\n   1. The applicant should be Class XII passed or its equivalent examination from recognized Boards/Councils with 50% marks with 5% relaxation for ST/SC/OBC/PWD.\n   1. A candidate waiting for Class - XII results may also apply with the condition that they can produce their provisional/original documents at the time of counseling.\n   1. The age of the applicant should be between 18 to 27 years and age relaxation will be up to 5 years for SC/ST/OBC/PWD as per the reservation policy of the government of Meghalaya. \n\n**Note:** There will be block-wise allocation of seats to facilitate the availability of trained teachers locally in the respective blocks.\n&gt; **Reservation Policy:**\n\n\n  - As per the Meghalaya Government Reservation Policy for different communities of the state.\n  - 5% of the seats will be reserved for persons with disabilities.\n\n&gt; **Marks allotment for the counseling:**\n\n**Sl. No.****Descriptions****Marks Allotment**1Academic (% of marks in Class XII)i. Marks with 80 – 100%50ii. Marks with 60 -79% 40iii. Marks with 60 -79% 302Entrance test marks503Personality104Communication Skills105Aptitude &amp;amp;amp;amp; interest towards teaching 206General Knowledge107Maximum Marks150**Note 01:** Waiting list candidates should be selected equivalent to the intake capacity of the institute.\n**Note 02:** The number of candidates for each counseling shall be decided by the respective DIETs.\n**Note 03:** In case the number of selected candidates is less than the intake capacity, in such cases, the institution should give preference to the waiting list from other districts as well.\n&gt; **Allotment of seats:**\n\nAt least 30% of the seats are to be allotted to candidates having Science and Mathematics backgrounds at the Class – XII level.\n",
